high performance, why the majority is always wrong and how you can use that to get everything

01:44.760 --> 01:52.320
you can out of everything you've got. But let me first introduce you to something interesting,

01:52.320 --> 01:57.000
an interesting observation. When people, teams and organizations, whenever they hit a wall,

01:57.000 --> 02:04.720
they tend to do one of two things. They either do more of the same things or they do less of the

02:04.760 --> 02:11.640
same things. But what you very seldom see is that they start to do different things instead. And

02:11.640 --> 02:16.280
it's interesting if you look at the data, approximately 3% of people are inclined to even

02:16.280 --> 02:24.440
do different things. And the remaining 97% continues to smash into the wall, like some kind of crazy

02:24.440 --> 02:32.160
energy bunny on steroids. And why is that? Why is that? And to understand what is going on here,

02:32.440 --> 02:36.120
